---
to: "service.proto"
description: "Generate gRPC service definition with Protobuf"
category: api
requires:
  - service_name
  - package_name
variables:
  service_name: "Service name"
  package_name: "Protobuf package name (e.g., myservice.v1)"
  version: "API version (default: v1)"
  java_package: "Java package name (default: com.example.myservice)"
  go_package: "Go package name (default: ./service)"
  services: "Array of service definitions (name, methods, rpcs)"
  messages: "Array of message type definitions"
  enums: "Array of enum definitions"
mode: overwrite



---







syntax = "proto3";

package {{ package_name }};

option java_package = "{{ java_package | default("com.example." + service_name | lower) }}";
option go_package = "{{ go_package | default("./" + service_name | lower) }}";

// Imports
{% for import in imports | default([]) %}
import "{{ import }}";
{% endfor %}

## Enums

{% for enum in enums | default([{name: "Status", values: [{name: "UNKNOWN", value: 0}, {name: "ACTIVE", value: 1}, {name: "INACTIVE", value: 2}]}]) %}
enum {{ enum.name }} {
{% for value in enum.values %}
  {{ value.name | upper }} = {{ value.value }};
{% endfor %}
}
{% endfor %}

## Messages

{% for message in messages | default([{name: "GetUserRequest", fields: [{name: "user_id", type: "string", number: 1}]}, {name: "GetUserResponse", fields: [{name: "user", type: "User"}]}, {name: "User", fields: [{name: "id", type: "string", number: 1}, {name: "name", type: "string", number: 2}, {name: "email", type: "string", number: 3}]}]) %}
message {{ message.name }} {
{% for field in message.fields %}
  {{ field.type }} {{ field.name }} = {{ field.number | default(loop.index) }};
{% endfor %}
}

{% endfor %}

## Services

{% for service in services | default([{name: "UserService", methods: [{name: "GetUser", request_type: "GetUserRequest", response_type: "GetUserResponse"}]}]) %}
service {{ service.name }} {
{% for method in service.methods %}
  rpc {{ method.name }} ({{ method.request_type }}) returns ({{ method.response_type }}) {
    // {{ method.description | default("RPC method for " + method.name) }}
  }
{% endfor %}
}

{% endfor %}

## Signal Theory

**Signal**: `S=(linguistic, specification, inform, proto, grpc-spec)`
- **Mode**: linguistic
- **Genre**: specification
- **Type**: inform
- **Format**: proto
- **Structure**: grpc-spec

## Usage

```bash
# Generate gRPC proto file
unrdf template render \
  --template packages/cli/templates/api/grpc-proto.njk \
  --service-name "UserService" \
  --package-name "myservice.v1"

# Generate server code
protoc --go_out=. --go-grpc_out=. service.proto

# Generate client code
protoc --python_out=. service.proto

# Generate documentation
protoc --doc_out=. --doc_opt=markdown,index.md service.proto
```

## gRPC Best Practices

1. **Use descriptive names** - Service and method names should be clear
2. **Version your APIs** - Use package versioning (e.g., v1, v2)
3. **Handle streaming** - Use `stream` keyword for bidirectional streaming
4. **Add comments** - Document all RPC methods and messages
5. **Use proper field numbers** - Reserve field numbers 1-15 for frequently used fields

## Streaming Example

```protobuf
service ChatService {
  rpc SendMessage (stream MessageRequest) returns (stream MessageResponse) {
    // Bidirectional streaming for chat messages
  }

  rpc GetMessages (GetMessagesRequest) returns (stream MessageResponse) {
    // Server streaming for message history
  }
}
```

